# Portfolio — Project Context

Personal portfolio for **Frederick Aurelio Halim**. Updating from 2024 → 2026 content.

## Stack
Next.js 16 · React 19 · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS 4 · GSAP · bilingual EN/中文

## Key files
- `src/utils/data.ts` — **all copy** (hero, projects, details, stacks, navbar)
- `src/app/page.tsx` — section order
- `src/context/TextContext.tsx` — language toggle (`en` | `ch`)
- `public/` — images, fonts, screenshots

## Workflow
1. User picks a task from `PORTFOLIO_PLAN.md` by ID (e.g. H1, M2, L1)
2. Apply `portfolio-writing` rules for any copy changes
3. Check off the task in `PORTFOLIO_PLAN.md` when done
4. User provides facts first; agent structures and implements — never invent metrics or job history

## Content rules (summary)
- Show what you built and why — not adjective bios
- Problem → decision → outcome for projects
- 3–5 curated projects max on homepage
- EN and 中文 must match facts (not fluffy machine translation)

## Extended docs
- `AGENTS.md` — full agent guide
- `PORTFOLIO_PLAN.md` — task checklist
- `PORTFOLIO_WRITING_RULES.md` — full writing reference with examples

## Code change scope
- Minimal diffs; match existing patterns (`"use client"`, `@/` imports, GSAP in sections)
- Do not commit unless user asks
- Do not add unrelated features when doing content updates
